Yarn Plug'n'Play replaces the way node resolves modules.
It removes the node_modules directory and does all module resolution through a file it generates called pnp.cjs.
This file is generated based on what's in your package.json file.
If you try to import an indirect dependency, yarn will throw an error.

Run these like this:

```
corepack yarn install

# works
corepack yarn node 1-use-direct-dependency.js

# fails
corepack yarn node 2-use-indirect-dependency.js
corepack yarn node 3-use-distant-node-module.js
```

corepack is the package manager for your package manager.
